
Commands and its uses:

1-  django-admin startproject mysite
Use:- This command creates a project

2-  py manage.py runserver
Use:-  Runs the development server

3-  py manage.py runserver 8080
Use:- Changes the running server port to 8080 (By default the server runs at 8000 port)

4-  py manage.py startapp appName
Use:- The above command creates an app inside the project

NOTE:- After creating any app in the project add the app in the INSTALLED_APPS in the settings.py
        file of the project

5-  python manage.py makemigrations polls
Use:-  By running makemigrations, you’re telling Django that you’ve made some changes to your models
        and that you’d like the changes to be stored as a migration.

6-  python manage.py sqlmigrate polls 0001
Use:- Creates the sql for the named migration

7-  python manage.py check
Use:- Checks any problem in the project without touching the database and without doing any migrations

8-  python manage.py migrate
Use:-  The migrate command takes all the migrations that haven’t been applied (Django tracks which ones are
        applied using a special table in your database called django_migrations) and runs them against your
        database - essentially, synchronizing the changes you made to your models with the schema in the database.

NOTE:-  The three steps for creating the models
        =>Change your models (in models.py).
        =>Run python manage.py makemigrations to create migrations for those changes
        =>Run python manage.py migrate to apply those changes to the database.

9-  python manage.py createsuperuser
Use:-  To create the admin login for django admin page

10-  If you want to edit any model through django admin then you havev to register the model in admin.py file of the app

